abstract: President Donald Trump marked the 20th anniversary Friday of federal legislation to help combat human trafficking by dedicating a new White House position to the issue.
snippet: President Donald Trump marked the 20th anniversary Friday of federal legislation to help combat human trafficking by dedicating a new White House position to the issue.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump marked the 20th anniversary Friday of federal legislation to help combat human trafficking by dedicating a new White House position to the issue.
headline_main: Trump Signs Order Creating Post Focused on Human Trafficking
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs Order Creating Post Focused on Human Trafficking

abstract: Palestinians held demonstrations across the region Friday to protest President Donald Trump's Middle East initiative, while militants in the Gaza Strip fired rockets and mortar rounds at Israel, drawing retaliatory strikes.
snippet: Palestinians held demonstrations across the region Friday to protest President Donald Trump's Middle East initiative, while militants in the Gaza Strip fired rockets and mortar rounds at Israel, drawing retaliatory strikes.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Palestinians held demonstrations across the region Friday to protest President Donald Trump's Middle East initiative, while militants in the Gaza Strip fired rockets and mortar rounds at Israel, drawing retaliatory strikes.
headline_main: Palestinians Protest Trump Plan, Gaza Militants Fire Rockets
headline_print_headline: Palestinians Protest Trump Plan, Gaza Militants Fire Rockets

abstract: Brexit, Coronavirus, Kobe Bryant: Here’s what you need to know.
snippet: Brexit, Coronavirus, Kobe Bryant: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: When the sun rises over Britain on Saturday, the country will no longer be part of the European Union.

abstract: Having bet it all on stopping Brexit and lost, Remainers now look to keeping Britain as close to the European Union as possible.
snippet: Having bet it all on stopping Brexit and lost, Remainers now look to keeping Britain as close to the European Union as possible.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — They marched by the hundreds of thousands to stop Brexit. They mourned when Prime Minister Boris Johnson walloped their side in the latest election.

abstract: The senator said he’d vote no on the question of witnesses on Friday, meaning Republicans are likely to be able to block the move for new evidence in the trial.
snippet: The senator said he’d vote no on the question of witnesses on Friday, meaning Republicans are likely to be able to block the move for new evidence in the trial.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lamar Alexander, Republican of Tennessee, said late Thursday that although he believed that Democrats have proved their case that President Trump had acted “inappropriately” in his dealings with Ukraine, he did not think the president’s actions were impeachable and he would vote against considering new evidence in the impeachment trial.

headline_main: Alexander says Democrats proved their case, but it’s not impeachable.

abstract: Democrats would need four Republicans to side with them on Friday to demand new witnesses and documents.
snippet: Democrats would need four Republicans to side with them on Friday to demand new witnesses and documents.
lead_paragraph: Senator Susan Collins, Republican of Maine, said late Thursday that she would vote in favor of considering additional witnesses and documents in the impeachment trial of President Trump.
